# Deny Destructive Git Operations
# Prevents accidental data loss from irreversible git commands.

NEVER run these commands without explicit user confirmation:

- `git push --force` or `git push -f` (overwrites remote history)
- `git reset --hard` (discards uncommitted changes)
- `git clean -fd` or `git clean -f` (deletes untracked files permanently)
- `git checkout -- <file>` (discards working tree changes)
- `git branch -D` (force-deletes branch without merge check)
- `git stash drop` (permanently removes stash entry)

If a task requires any of these, STOP and explain the risk before proceeding.
